and learn to sing them yourself.

06:27.387 --> 06:28.684
Slavery is over.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.724
Really? You're not gonna
sing any more?

06:30.891 --> 06:32.689
No.

06:34.477 --> 06:36.696
Assume the position. What?

06:40.025 --> 06:41.368
Whoop. Ha-ha.

07:05.842 --> 07:09.767
Y'all are late, and she's up.

07:18.813 --> 07:20.565
Shh.

07:22.317 --> 07:24.490
Sparkle. Hush.
Sorry.

07:25.654 --> 07:27.076
Shh!

07:32.494 --> 07:34.622
Hurry.

07:37.123 --> 07:39.376
What y'all doing in there?

07:50.679 --> 07:52.647
My babies.

07:53.056 --> 07:55.354
But I know y'all don't
love each other that much.

07:56.351 --> 07:58.524
Sister and Sparkle, curl your hair.

07:58.687 --> 08:00.689
Church in the morning.

08:00.855 --> 08:01.902
You hear me?

08:02.774 --> 08:06.244
Dolores, why is my window open?
I'm not trying to heat the outside.

08:08.363 --> 08:09.580
Close it.

08:09.739 --> 08:11.286
- Good night.
- Good night.

08:14.119 --> 08:15.712
Is she gone?

08:15.870 --> 08:18.919
Y'all heifers sneak out,
and I get fussed at?

08:20.542 --> 08:22.544
Laugh at... Laugh at that.
Is that funny?

08:22.919 --> 08:24.216
Peace be with you.

08:24.379 --> 08:27.132
And also with you.

08:30.051 --> 08:33.020
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

08:33.179 --> 08:39.027
You know, the Lord loves a church
full of happy, good-looking black folk.

08:39.184 --> 08:40.562
Amen!

08:40.729 --> 08:42.572
I know y'all
happy this morning, right?

08:42.731 --> 08:43.823
Yes!

08:43.982 --> 08:47.907
Ain't no frowns in
this church today, is there?

08:48.653 --> 08:51.702
No frowns, no clowns,
not in church.

08:51.865 --> 08:53.458
And look at the choir.

08:53.616 --> 08:55.914
- How y'all doing this morning?
- Good!

08:56.077 --> 08:58.375
Levi, there she go.
What? What?

08:58.538 --> 09:01.712
Seven Sundays, seven churches,
and $7 later, and I find her.

09:01.875 --> 09:03.548
- That light-skinned girl?
- There.

09:03.710 --> 09:05.678
Oh, man. Well, that's Tammy Anderson.

09:05.837 --> 09:08.386
Yeah, man, she is smoking hot.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.175
Tammy.
Two sisters. They all fine.

09:10.341 --> 09:12.093
They can all sing too.
Is that right?

09:12.260 --> 09:14.979
Sure, you're right.
But they mama crazy, though.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.019
Shh!

09:17.182 --> 09:19.776
Y'all know better.

09:19.934 --> 09:23.734
I know I can't sing,
but I can love to hear singing.

09:23.897 --> 09:25.149
- Yes!
- Right?

09:28.193 --> 09:31.618
I'll see you next week, right?
Okay. See you later.

09:32.280 --> 09:35.329
Excuse me. You was
at the Discovery a few weeks...

09:35.492 --> 09:36.960
Shh.
...ago.

09:42.040 --> 09:45.169
Oh... Bible study's
at your house this week?

09:45.335 --> 09:46.882
Yeah, it is.

09:47.045 --> 09:48.422
You know, you bad at this.

09:50.131 --> 09:51.974
Just act natural.

09:52.842 --> 09:54.139
Hi. My name's Stix.

09:54.302 --> 09:55.599
Sparkle.

09:56.221 --> 09:57.564
Sara.
Huh?

09:57.722 --> 10:01.147
Who is my baby talking to?
Nineteen ain't no baby no more, Emma.

10:02.352 --> 10:05.231
What? No need in eyeballing me.
I tells the truth.

10:05.396 --> 10:07.023
It's in my contract as your friend.

10:07.565 --> 10:09.988
I'm telling you,
you hold on too tight to that one,

10:10.151 --> 10:12.995
she'll be unmarried
and back on your doorstep like Sister.

10:14.322 --> 10:16.120
That's just temporary, okay?

10:16.282 --> 10:19.206
Well, New York just spit her
right on back out, huh?

10:19.369 --> 10:20.495
No.
You know what?

10:20.662 --> 10:23.336
<i>You worry about your daughter,
I'll worry about mine.</i>

10:23.498 --> 10:25.171
I'm just saying.
Yeah, what?

10:25.333 --> 10:26.710
- Mom, I need some money.
- What?

10:26.876 --> 10:29.675
They selling dinners in the basement,
and they going fast.

10:29.838 --> 10:30.885
Mom?
Don't do it.

10:31.047 --> 10:32.674
Mama, please.
Come with me.

10:32.841 --> 10:34.013
Now you stop.
See y'all later.

10:42.016 --> 10:44.018
Sparkle.

10:44.185 --> 10:45.732
Let's go.

10:46.563 --> 10:50.534
So I will see you
at Bible study, Sparkle?

10:51.734 --> 10:53.327
Maybe.

11:03.788 --> 11:06.883
<i>Another one of my white friends
came to me the other day and said,</i>

11:07.041 --> 11:09.715
<i>"Where's the best place
to hide something from a Negro</i>

11:09.878 --> 11:11.255
<i>and he'll never find it?"</i>

11:11.421 --> 11:13.640
<i>I told him, "A work boot."</i>

11:16.384 --> 11:18.182
Y'all know he talking about us, right?

11:18.344 --> 11:19.812
<i>People are always asking me...</i>

11:20.555 --> 11:22.148
Where is she?
I don't know.

11:22.640 --> 11:26.270
Ms. Anderson, where's the bathroom?
Down the hall, second door to the right.

11:26.436 --> 11:27.562
Second door.
Mm-hm.

11:27.729 --> 11:29.231
Thank you.
Yeah, second door.

11:29.856 --> 11:33.736
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, Satin Struthers.
Let's give him a hand.</i>

11:33.902 --> 11:36.997
<i>Great job. Thanks for coming.
Isn't he funny?</i>

11:39.699 --> 11:40.746
There you are.

11:41.409 --> 11:43.457
Why you not in Bible study?

11:43.620 --> 11:45.122
Haven't you heard?

11:45.288 --> 11:48.508
I'm a heathen. Don't want to sit in there
and be a hypocrite.

11:48.666 --> 11:50.634
Well, we already
got something in common,

11:50.793 --> 11:54.388
because I only came
just so I could ask you out.

11:56.341 --> 11:59.094
The other door. To the right.

11:59.260 --> 12:01.729
Other door. Sorry.

12:10.647 --> 12:13.116
Oh, y'all like that, huh?

12:13.274 --> 12:16.323
Funky dance, huh? You like that.
You like that music? Funky, huh?

12:17.111 --> 12:18.954
It make you want to dance.
Come on.

12:19.113 --> 12:20.239
Get it, Mama.

12:20.406 --> 12:22.875
Uh-huh. Yeah, Mama gonna get it.
Mama gonna get it.

12:23.034 --> 12:24.627
And you will too.

12:24.786 --> 12:27.460
You keep dancing like that,
you'll bring home a baby you can't feed.

12:29.123 --> 12:30.170
Let's open our Bibles.

12:30.959 --> 12:32.461
Oh.

12:32.627 --> 12:36.097
The deal was color television
for an hour of Bible study.

12:36.798 --> 12:39.642
I lived up to my end,
now you live up to yours.

12:40.635 --> 12:42.729
So let's go to Psalms 10...

12:42.887 --> 12:46.312
Reverend Bryce called.
Says he need you to check the books.

12:46.474 --> 12:49.648
The numbers are not adding up.

12:52.313 --> 12:53.940
All right.

12:57.819 --> 12:59.241
What are you watching?

13:01.990 --> 13:04.869
Oh, I love this song.

13:11.791 --> 13:14.761
No, no. Too many hormones
unattended in here.

13:14.919 --> 13:17.763
Let's go. Get out. Come on.
Sister, turn that TV off.

13:17.922 --> 13:20.220
Thank you. Come on, let's go.

13:20.383 --> 13:21.851
- Bye, Sparkle.
- See you.

13:22.010 --> 13:25.059
Good night, Mama.
Good night, baby.

13:25.221 --> 13:27.098
Mm. It was just getting good.

13:27.265 --> 13:28.608
See you tonight, Sparkle.

13:28.766 --> 13:31.315
- Call you later.
- All right.

13:31.477 --> 13:32.820
See you next time.

13:32.979 --> 13:35.448
- Bye, Tammy.
- Bye, Tune.

13:38.192 --> 13:40.570
Well, good night.

13:40.737 --> 13:42.410
Good night.

13:47.744 --> 13:51.749
Why are all the cute ones
always so stupid?

13:52.498 --> 13:55.126
Hey, can I talk to you for a second?

14:03.634 --> 14:06.012
All right, I'm going.

14:40.880 --> 14:45.681
♪ You bring out
The woman in me ♪

14:45.843 --> 14:50.815
♪ What can I say
That you can't see? ♪

14:50.973 --> 14:55.149
♪ I like the way we carry on ♪

14:55.311 --> 15:01.239
♪ Hope you understand
My feelings got me just reelin' ♪

15:01.401 --> 15:06.328
♪ What can I do
With this feelin'? ♪

15:06.489 --> 15:10.084
♪ Hooked on your love
Sweet love, love ♪

15:11.494 --> 15:16.500
♪ What can I do
With this feelin'? ♪

15:16.666 --> 15:22.093
♪ Hooked on your love
Sweet love, mm ♪♪

15:22.255 --> 15:23.598
Please, don't stop.

15:23.756 --> 15:26.179
What are you still doing here?
That was beautiful.

15:26.509 --> 15:27.681
Mm.

15:29.303 --> 15:31.146
Wait, that's your song?
You wrote that?

15:31.305 --> 15:32.978
Only if you thought it was good.

15:33.141 --> 15:34.484
I thought it was phenomenal.

15:34.642 --> 15:36.895
Then I wrote it.

15:37.061 --> 15:39.564
So did you write that song
your sister sang

15:39.730 --> 15:42.199
at the Discovery a few weeks back?

15:43.192 --> 15:46.412
Yes, but she kind of made it her own.
Wait a minute.

15:46.571 --> 15:48.323
You wrote that song?

15:48.489 --> 15:50.537
You wrote the song you were singing?

15:50.700 --> 15:53.954
You wrote the songs in here too?

15:54.120 --> 15:56.168
Yes. Ahem.

15:56.330 --> 15:58.173
What you gonna do with the music?

15:58.332 --> 16:00.334
Why not? Nothing.

16:01.127 --> 16:03.846
Because my mother
would never let me.

16:04.005 --> 16:07.555
Plus, I'm not the singer in the family.
Sister is, then Dee.

16:07.717 --> 16:10.266
I sing in the choir
so I don't sit by myself in church.

16:10.428 --> 16:12.772
No offense,
but I'm just hearing excuses.

16:12.930 --> 16:14.603
Excuse me?
I don't mean to be rude.

16:14.765 --> 16:17.769
I'm just passionate,
especially when it comes down to music.

16:17.935 --> 16:20.688
That's why I'm here.
I'm staying with my cousin, Levi.

16:20.855 --> 16:24.155
I'm from Kansas City.
We got a cool jazz scene down there.

16:24.317 --> 16:27.742
I managed a few acts,
but the money's here in Motown.

16:27.904 --> 16:29.998
And I want to be...
I am the next Berry Gordy.

16:30.156 --> 16:32.705
I figure, his stomach ain't
growling like mine any more.

16:32.867 --> 16:35.120
Maybe he's leaving a lot
of steak and potatoes out there.

16:37.872 --> 16:39.795
You mind if I hear that song again?

16:41.209 --> 16:43.962
Mm. Still needs a lot of work.

17:00.061 --> 17:01.483
Why won't you unpack?

17:01.646 --> 17:03.648
I really don't plan on
being here that long.

17:04.315 --> 17:05.907
You said that two months ago.

17:09.654 --> 17:11.406
Sorry.

17:12.531 --> 17:16.377
Hey, don't ever be sorry
for telling the truth, Spark.

17:18.079 --> 17:19.830
What was that?

17:25.502 --> 17:27.300
Your Romeo is out there.

17:27.463 --> 17:29.340
What?
Mm-hm.

17:44.230 --> 17:46.449
You can't be throwing rocks
at my window.

17:46.607 --> 17:47.779
My mother has a gun.

17:49.652 --> 17:51.620
A gun. A big one.

17:51.779 --> 17:53.781
There's an underground club tonight.

17:53.948 --> 17:56.042
The kind that songwriters
don't want to miss.

17:56.200 --> 17:57.747
You got to hear the music.

17:57.910 --> 18:00.288
It's the stuff they ain't playing
on the radio.

18:00.454 --> 18:04.004
Come with me.
He wants me to go hear music with him.

18:05.001 --> 18:08.471
You've snuck out
of the house for less.

18:08.629 --> 18:10.757
And I know just the dress.

18:12.800 --> 18:14.222
You coming?

18:57.928 --> 18:59.851
I ain't gonna bite you.

19:00.014 --> 19:02.142
And how do I know that?

19:03.267 --> 19:05.611
You're gonna have to trust me.

19:40.137 --> 19:41.605
Can I tell you something?

19:41.764 --> 19:44.438
I think your lyrics are too safe.

19:44.600 --> 19:47.570
I mean, you got Dr. King, the war.

19:49.105 --> 19:52.985
I don't think the metaphorical lyrics
gonna fly any more.

19:53.150 --> 19:54.823
What?
You impressed by my big word?

19:54.985 --> 19:57.158
I was.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.542
In the spirit of telling the truth,
can I tell you another?

20:01.701 --> 20:04.705
I wouldn't want you to lie.
Then why do you lie to yourself?

20:06.288 --> 20:08.791
About not wanting to sing?

20:09.333 --> 20:11.256
I mean, Sparkle,
you writing these songs.

20:11.419 --> 20:13.342
And you can sing.

20:14.296 --> 20:18.301
So why aren't you singing them?
I'm no Diana or Aretha.

20:20.094 --> 20:21.687
You know, you right.

20:21.846 --> 20:23.848
You Sparkle.

20:25.266 --> 20:29.191
